overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, providing both the Statement of Work and the detailed
  questionnaire content. The goal was to verify that all acceptance criteria
  were met and to identify any missing functionalities. The review involved
  examining the codebase, including database schema, API endpoints for responses
  and PDF generation, and various questionnaire components and sections. The
  analysis confirmed that core functionalities like the interactive
  questionnaire, database storage, CSV export (for demographics), PDF report
  generation, and an admin dashboard are in place. Most specified sleep
  disorders are detected, and essential sleep metrics are calculated. However,
  the review also highlighted several critical gaps. High-priority missing items
  include a detailed tiredness severity scale with safety warnings, explicit
  detection for Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA), the inclusion of
  outbound educational and clinician links in the reports, and robust detection
  for Insufficient Sleep Syndrome. Other notable omissions were weighted scoring
  for Excessive Daytime Sleepiness, comprehensive pain and medical history
  questions, and a complete CSV export of all questionnaire responses. The
  findings provide a clear roadmap for further development to fully align the
  application with the project's requirements.
